[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (2) **Coordination-decision-record journal, longitudinal coordination state, provenance journal, seam-flag store, referral-lifecycle store, transition-of-care store, sensitive-disclosure flow, and tool-call ledger accumulate multi-year cross-organizational PHI-rich free-text outside archive-reference pattern, with recipe-distinct provenance-journal-as-separately-keyed and 42-CFR-Part-2-substance-use-treatment-data and state-specific-mental-health-record-and-HIV-record-and-genetic-test-result protections and Information-Blocking-rule-data-sharing-posture amplifications.** Same chapter pattern as 11.4-11.8 with recipe-distinct cross-organizational and additionally-protected-PHI extensions. The Step 6E persist_coordination_decision_record write includes the full composed_response, full citations, full active-version stamps. The Step 2E provenance journal write captures source data with separate KMS keying (good, partial credit) but the architecture does not specify the per-record-class access-control surface, the patient-right-of-access-and-deletion workflow, or the retention reconciliation across HIPAA's six-year minimum, state-specific medical-record retention rules, 42 CFR Part 2 retention for substance-use-treatment-data where applicable, state-specific mental-health/HIV/genetic-test-result statutes, FDA SaMD post-market obligations, and litigation-hold obligations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (3) **Per-cohort referral-closure-rate-and-transition-completion-rate-and-medication-reconciliation-accuracy-and-seam-detection-precision-and-recall-and-engagement-attrition-and-citation-coverage-and-equity-disparity-and-integration-coverage monitoring with launch-gate discipline architecturally implicit despite recipe's own elevation as central trap, with recipe-distinct integration-coverage-disparity-as-equity-acute and per-cohort-coordination-outcome-disparity extensions.** Same chapter pattern as 11.1-11.8 Finding A1 with recipe-distinct cross-organizational and integration-coverage extensions. The recipe correctly elevates per-cohort monitoring in five separate places. Despite this thorough prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode (Step 10 reporting iteration) do not specify per-cohort launch-gate threshold values, two-axis and three-axis cohort stratification, per-cohort referral-closure rate per specialty, per-cohort transition-completion rate per transition type, per-cohort medication-reconciliation accuracy with pharmacy-informatics-partnership-flag, per-cohort seam-detection precision and recall per rule with named clinical-leadership-ownership-flag, per-cohort engagement-attrition rate at 30/90/180/360-day windows with caregiver-burden-driver annotation, per-cohort citation-coverage rate (target 95%+), per-cohort regulatory-disclaimer-presence rate, per-cohort conservative-bias-compliance rate, per-cohort scope-violation rate, per-cohort sensitive-disclosure handling completeness, per-cohort mandatory-reporting routing completeness, per-cohort PROM trajectories with appropriate attribution caveats, per-cohort 30-day-readmission-rate and ED-utilization-rate change with attribution caveats, per-cohort patient-and-caregiver-reported coordination experience, per-cohort relationship-quality signals, per-cohort tool-call-failure rate per tool, per-cohort integration-coverage profile (well-instrumented vs partially-instrumented vs poorly-instrumented), per-cohort equity-disparity flags by sex, race, age, language, social-determinant flag, and integration-coverage profile with statistical-significance flags. Recipe-acute amplification because patients with the highest coordination needs are often the patients with the most limited access to digital tools and the most limited integration coverage; per-cohort variation in integration-coverage profile is the recipe-distinct equity-acute metric.
