[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The sensitive-disclosure flow** for caregiver-burden, caregiver-abuse, elder-abuse, intimate-partner violence, financial-exploitation, substance-use crisis, and food/housing/transportation-barrier disclosures requires careful handling with separately-managed KMS keying, restricted-access-only surfacing, mandatory-reporting routing for relevant categories, and per-state-statute retention. The recipe references this in Step 4B but does not architecturally elevate the sensitive-disclosure store as a separate record class.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The per-record-class access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer. The longitudinal-store's access-control surface is the patient's care team (with consent) plus the patient (per HIPAA right-of-access). The coordination-decision-record-journal's access-control surface is the clinical leadership plus operations plus compliance plus audit-and-compliance plus the data-science team for outcome-correlation plus the patient (through the institution's patient-record-access pathway). The provenance journal's access-control surface is restricted to compliance plus audit-and-compliance plus malpractice insurer plus regulatory team plus clinical leadership only (recipe-distinct restricted access for blast-radius containment). Each record class has different access-control needs.
